procedures.name: Venipuncture
procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation, viral screening, and pregnancy testing.

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.name: Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of urine samples for measurement of copper and molybdenum content, urinalysis, drug screening, and pregnancy testing. Includes 24-hour urine collection.

code.decode: Urinalysis, by dip stick or tablet reagent

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Stool Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of fecal samples for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A complete physical examination including assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: Electrocardiogram
procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate and intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc).

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.name: Anthropometric Measurement
procedures.label: Height, Weight, BMI
procedures.description: Measurement of height, weight, and calculation of Body Mass Index (BMI).

procedures.name: Clinical Laboratory Assessment
procedures.label: Lab Tests
procedures.description: Laboratory assessments including serum chemistry, hematology, and coagulation.

procedures.name: Pregnancy Test
procedures.label: Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Urine and/or serum pregnancy tests for females of childbearing potential.

code.decode: Urine pregnancy test, by visual color comparison methods

procedures.name: Bowel and Urine Monitoring
procedures.label: Intake/Output Monitoring
procedures.description: Monitoring of urination and bowel movements, including menstruation checks for female participants.

procedures.name: Viral Screening
procedures.label: HIV, Hepatitis B/C Screen
procedures.description: Screening for Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV), Hepatitis B, and Hepatitis C.

procedures.name: Drug Screening
procedures.label: Urine Drug Screen
procedures.description: Screening for drugs of abuse via urine sample.

procedures.name: Alcohol Test
procedures.label: Alcohol Test
procedures.description: Test to screen for alcohol use.

medicalDevices.name: Cannula
medicalDevices.label: Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula may be placed to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

medicalDevices.name: Catheter
medicalDevices.label: Catheter
medicalDevices.description: A catheter may be used for venous access but not left in place for longer than 72 hours.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure Monitor
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Monitor
medicalDevices.description: A completely automated device for assessing blood pressure and heart rate.
